### ZimCrimeWatch API - REST Client Test File
### Compatible with: VS Code REST Client extension, JetBrains HTTP Client
###
### USAGE
### -----
### 1. Run Login first — copy the returned `access` and `refresh` values
### 2. Paste them into the @accessToken / @refreshToken variables below
### 3. Run any other request
###
### Variables
@baseUrl       = http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
@contentType   = application/json
@accessToken   = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ0b2tlbl90eXBlIjoiYWNjZXNzIiwiZXhwIjoxNzcyNTg3NDM2LCJpYXQiOjE3NzI1ODM4MzYsImp0aSI6IjBjY2VhMzdjODBhYTQ3ODhhN2MwYWMzYzhjNmE2ZDQzIiwidXNlcl9pZCI6IjEifQ.ZZsraOV624-TD70vI1gMINKjYjx4NoqTZwyVpEila18
@refreshToken  = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ0b2tlbl90eXBlIjoicmVmcmVzaCIsImV4cCI6MTc3MjY3MDIzNiwiaWF0IjoxNzcyNTgzODM2LCJqdGkiOiIxZmZhMTM0M2JlYmI0YmY0YTNlMzkwZmM3YTQ1MTJhYiIsInVzZXJfaWQiOiIxIn0.rmYWSg8MUxZCJn4-z_sqJpJbXxw5rnxblkqb_ptjtQ8
@badgeNumber   = 1234
@password      = qwerty1234

###############################################################################
# 1. AUTHENTICATION
###############################################################################

### 1.1 Login — obtain access + refresh token pair
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/login/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 1.2 Refresh access token
# Send current refresh token → receive new access token
# (If ROTATE_REFRESH_TOKENS=True, a new refresh token is also returned)
# @name tokenRefresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/token/refresh/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refresh": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.3 Logout — blacklist the refresh token
# After this call the refresh token is permanently invalid.
# The access token remains valid until it expires (default 15 min).
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/logout/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "refresh": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.4 Login — invalid credentials (expect 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/login/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "ZRP-000000",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### 1.5 Login — missing password field (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/login/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "zrp_badge_number": "{{badgeNumber}}"
}

###

### 1.6 Refresh — invalid token (expect 400 / 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/auth/token/refresh/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refresh": "this.is.not.a.valid.token"
}


###############################################################################
# 2. PUBLIC ENDPOINTS  (no authentication required)
###############################################################################

### 2.1 Get anonymized crime map pins (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.2 Filter public crimes by crime_type_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?crime_type_id=1
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.3 Filter public crimes by suburb
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?suburb=Mbare
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.4 Filter public crimes by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-12-31
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.5 Filter public crimes — combined filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crimes/?crime_type_id=2&suburb=Avondale&start_date=2024-06-01&end_date=2024-12-31
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2.6 Get all crime types + icons (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/crime-types/
Accept: {{contentType}}


###############################################################################
# 3. ZRP DASHBOARD — INCIDENT CRUD  (JWT required)
###############################################################################

### 3.1 List all incidents
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.2 List incidents filtered by crime type
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/?crime_type_id=1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.3 List incidents filtered by suburb + status
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/?suburb=Harare+CBD&status=under_investigation
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.4 List incidents filtered by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/?start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-06-30
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.5 Create a new incident
# latitude + longitude are submitted as plain floats;
# the backend converts them to a PostGIS Point internally.
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "case_number":            "ZRP-2024-00123",
  "crime_type":             1,
  "timestamp":              "2024-08-15T14:30:00Z",
  "latitude":               -17.8292,
  "longitude":              31.0522,
  "suburb":                 "Mbare",
  "description_narrative":  "Suspect broke rear window and stole laptop bag.",
  "modus_operandi":         "Smash and grab targeting parked vehicles near market.",
  "status":                 "reported",
  "weapon_used":            "Unknown",
  "num_suspects":           2,
  "serial_group_label":     ""
}

###

### 3.6 Create incident — missing required fields (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "suburb": "Avondale"
}

###

### 3.7 Create incident — duplicate case number (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "case_number": "ZRP-2024-00123",
  "crime_type":  1,
  "latitude":    -17.8292,
  "longitude":   31.0522
}

###

### 3.8 Get a single incident by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.9 Get non-existent incident (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/99999/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.10 Update (partial PATCH) an incident — change status + add coordinates
PUT {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "status":    "under_investigation",
  "latitude":  -17.8300,
  "longitude": 31.0530
}

###

### 3.11 Update incident — only move location (coordinates only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "latitude":  -17.7721,
  "longitude": 31.0447
}

###

### 3.12 Delete an incident (admin only — expect 403 for non-admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 3.13 Get similar cases for an incident (profile matching)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/similar/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.14 Get similar cases — custom top_n
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/1/similar/?top_n=10
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3.15 Access incidents without token (expect 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/incidents/
Accept: {{contentType}}


###############################################################################
# 4. ZRP DASHBOARD — CRIME TYPE CRUD  (JWT required)
###############################################################################

### 4.1 List all crime types with incident counts
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 4.2 Create a new crime type
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name":        "Cybercrime",
  "description": "Crimes involving computers, networks, or digital devices.",
  "icon":        "laptop-icon"
}

###

### 4.3 Create crime type — duplicate name (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Cybercrime"
}

###

### 4.4 Get a single crime type
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 4.5 Update a crime type
PUT {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "description": "Updated description for this crime category.",
  "icon":        "new-icon-slug"
}

###

### 4.6 Delete a crime type
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/zrp/crime-types/1/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


###############################################################################
# 5. ZRP DASHBOARD — KPI SUMMARY  (JWT required)
###############################################################################

### 5.1 Get dashboard summary (total incidents, last 7 days, last 30 days, by status, top types)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/dashboard/summary/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}


###############################################################################
# 6. ANALYTICS  (analyst + admin role required)
###############################################################################

### 6.1 Heatmap — GET with query params
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/heatmap/?crime_type_id=1&start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-12-31&bandwidth=0.01
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 6.2 Heatmap — POST with body
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/heatmap/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "crime_type_id": 1,
  "start_date":    "2024-01-01",
  "end_date":      "2024-12-31",
  "bandwidth":     0.01
}

###

### 6.3 Heatmap — all crime types, no date filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/heatmap/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 6.4 Time series — GET (weekly aggregation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/timeseries/?freq=W&start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 6.5 Time series — POST (monthly, specific crime type)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/timeseries/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "crime_type_id": 2,
  "start_date":    "2023-01-01",
  "end_date":      "2024-12-31",
  "freq":          "M"
}

###

### 6.6 Time series — daily frequency
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/timeseries/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "freq": "D",
  "start_date": "2024-06-01",
  "end_date":   "2024-06-30"
}

###

### 6.7 Hotspot detection — GET with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/hotspots/?crime_type_id=1&start_date=2024-01-01&end_date=2024-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 6.8 Hotspot detection — POST (no filters, all data)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/hotspots/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

###

### 6.9 Profile match — find similar cases to incident #1
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/profile-match/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "incident_id": 1,
  "top_n":       5
}

###

### 6.10 Profile match — larger result set
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/profile-match/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "incident_id": 1,
  "top_n":       20
}

###

### 6.11 Profile match — non-existent incident (expect 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/zrp/analytics/profile-match/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "incident_id": 99999,
  "top_n":       5
}


